Package: hiddenmeta
Title: Diagnosis and meta-analysis of hard-to-reach population studies
Version: 0.3.2
Authors@R: c(person("Georgiy", "Syunyaev", email = "gs2716@columbia.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"), , comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-4391-6313")),
             person("Macartan", "Humphreys", email = "macartan@gmail.com", role = c("aut"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-7029-2326")),
             person("Till", "Tietz", email = "ttietz2014@gmail.com", role = c("aut")))
Maintainer: Georgiy Syunyaev <gs2716@columbia.edu>
Description: Package allows analysis of individual and multiple studies of 
    hidden population size and prevalence using RDS, TLS or PPS samples. 
    The functions are written so that they can be used with DeclareDesign package to 
    allow for easy declaration of one or more studies with various sampling and estimation strategies. 
    Package implements functions for estimation of hidden population size and prevalance based on 
    using existing packages, such as RDS, sspse, Rcapture, SparseMSE, chords and networkscaleup.
